        body: "Hip pain is a common complaint that can stem from various causes, including arthritis, injuries, and structural abnormalities affecting the hip joint.",
        detail: "<p><strong>Hip pain</strong> is a common complaint that can significantly impact mobility and quality of life. The hip joint is a ball-and-socket joint that connects the thighbone (femur) to the pelvis, allowing for a wide range of motion while bearing the body's weight.</p><p>Hip pain can originate from within the joint itself (intra-articular) or from surrounding structures like muscles, tendons, bursae, or nerves. Common causes include <a href=\"/conditions/hip-arthritis\" class=\"text-blue-600 hover:underline\">hip arthritis</a>, <a href=\"/conditions/hip-impingement\" class=\"text-blue-600 hover:underline\">hip impingement</a>, <a href=\"/conditions/hip-labral-tear\" class=\"text-blue-600 hover:underline\">labral tears</a>, <a href=\"/conditions/hip-bursitis\" class=\"text-blue-600 hover:underline\">bursitis</a>, and <a href=\"/conditions/hip-fracture\" class=\"text-blue-600 hover:underline\">fractures</a>.</p><p>At Mountain Spine & Orthopedics, our <strong>hip specialists</strong> use comprehensive evaluation including physical examination, <strong>X-rays</strong>, <strong>MRI</strong>, and other advanced imaging to identify the exact cause of hip pain and create a personalized treatment plan that addresses both symptoms and underlying causes.</p>",
